Phishing is a type of cybercrime where attackers trick users into revealing sensitive information such as passwords or bank details. 
It usually happens through fake emails or messages that appear to be from trusted sources.
For example, a student may receive an email claiming to be from a bank asking to verify account details. 
When the student clicks the link and enters information, the attacker steals it.
Students and online users are common targets because they may not recognize fake links. 
The consequences include financial loss and identity theft.
Therefore, awareness and caution are important to avoid phishing attacks.
